-- Akin Gump Hires Ex-Lehman Director for Project Finance Practice
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-01-18T21:41:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/akin-gump-hires-ex-lehman-director-for-project-finance-practice.html
Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP 
hired Jacob J. Worenklein, a former managing director at  Lehman
Brothers (LEH) , to help the Dallas-based  law firm  expand its project
finance practice.  Worenklein, a lawyer, was most recently a partner at
 Bingham McCutchen LLP (1186L) . In addition to heading global project
finance and independent power at Lehman Brothers, Worenklein
also worked at  Milbank Tweed Hadley & McCloy LLP  and Societe
Generale SA, and is the former chief executive officer of  US
Power Generating Co (UPR) .  “His tremendous experience in guiding complex energy,
power, water and other infrastructure projects will be a great
asset to our clients and practice,” Ed Zaelke, co-head of Akin
Gump’s global project finance practice, said yesterday in a
statement.  Worenklein will be based in  New York  where he will serve as
co-head of the firm’s global project finance practice.  Akin Gump employs more than 800 lawyers in the U.S.,
 Europe ,  Asia  and the  Middle East .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Thomas in New York at 
